modules.description: This module enables template-driven code generation and AST manipulation by parsing OCaml expressions and types from strings, handling parameterized templates with typed defaults, and transforming XML-like structures into OCaml AST nodes. It operates on abstract syntax trees with location tracking, string-based template definitions, and custom parameter records, supporting use cases like embedding domain-specific languages or automating boilerplate code through PPX extensions. Key capabilities include mapping template attributes to OCaml types, expanding syntax extensions via declarative rules, and extracting/translating structured data from hierarchical templates.

This module enables template-driven code generation and AST manipulation by parsing OCaml expressions and types from strings, supporting parameterized templates with typed defaults, and transforming XML-like structures into OCaml AST nodes. It provides data types for abstract syntax trees with location tracking, string-based templates, and custom parameter records. Operations include mapping template attributes to OCaml types, expanding syntax extensions via declarative rules, and translating structured data from hierarchical templates. Example uses include embedding domain-specific languages and automating boilerplate code through PPX extensions.
